Cybersecurity defense 

Security Tools

Firewall - Filters network traffic and blocks unwanted connections.
Antivirus - Detects and removes malware.
VPN - Encrypts internet traffic and improves privacy.

IDS - Intrusion Detection System.    Detects suspicious activity.

IPS - Intrusion Prevention System.   Detects and blocks threats.

Security Best Practices

Keep software updated.
Use strong passwords.
Enable MFA.
Back up important files.
Be careful with emails and links.
Lock devices when not in use.
Follow company security policies.

Key Defense Principle
Defense in Depth

Use multiple layers of security.

Example: Strong password - MFA - Firewall - Antivirus - Security awareness

If one layer fails, another layer helps protect the system.



